The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	Mumbai: Suspended IPL chairman Lalit Modis legal counsel Mehmood Abdi rebutted charges of irregularities against his client regarding the awarding the IPLs theatrical rights against his client. Abdi also pointed the gun back at BCCI Secretary N Srinivasan by accusing the latter of creating hurdles in selling the theatrical rights and thereby incurring losses to the Board.        
	New Delhi: Rohan Bopanna joined Leander Paes in the doubles quarter finals of the UNICEF Open after clearing the first round with Aisam-ul-Haq Qureshi in sHertogenbosch, The Netherlands.        
	London: Indias Somdev Dev Varman crashed out of the Wimbledon singles qualifiers after losing to American Ryler Deheart lost 2-6, 7-6(2), 3-6. Harsh Mankad and his Serbian partner Ilija Bozoljac beat the Brazilian pair of Thiago Alves and Joao Souza 6-3, 7-6 (5) in the first round.        
	Vienna: Austrian tennis great and former No. 1 Thomas Muster announced his comeback to the ATP circuit at age of 42.         
	New Delhi: Dragflicker Sandeep Singh returned, while injured striker Shivendra Singh and midfielder Arjun Halappa were rested from a 22-member Indian hockey squad for a tour of Europe, starting next month.        
	Chennai: P V Nandhidhaa and Cholleti Sahajasri beat Bhakti Kulkarni and Hejazipour Mitra of Iran respectively in the second round of the Asian Junior Chess Championship.     
